com.github.methylene.sym

Class Lists

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.methylene.sym.Lists

  • public class Lists
extends Object

    This class contains immutable array based implementations of List that have efficient indexOf, lastIndexOf and contains methods.

    Per default it is not possible to construct a list that contains null values. This can be configured via the underlying PermutationFactory.

    Notes:

    • Performance gains over java.util.ArrayList are more significant when the return value of .indexOf is large, if the list is big and indexOf returns -1, or if the equals method of the list elements is expensive.
    • The List implementations do not implement List.subList(int, int).
    • Binary search is used for quick lookup, so all values in the lists must be Comparables, or a Comparator must be provided. If nulls are allowed, ony the Comparator makes sense, otherwise Arrays.binarySearch(long[], long) will throw an Exception.
    • Some of the implementations below use arrays of primitives directly and avoid boxing.
    See Also:
    PermutationFactory.getNullPolicy()
